"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-pressbox-press-releases-tonight-nbcuniversal-to-present-historic-moments-from-its-2024-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-coverage-on-sphere\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  NBCU's Highlights from Olympic Games Paris 2024's Opening Ceremony to be Presented on Sphere's LED Exterior    NBCU's Primetime West Coast Coverage on the Exosphere Includes Team USA's and Host Nation France's Boats Finishing Their Journey Down Paris' River Seine and the Lighting of the Olympic Cauldron  STAMFORD, Conn. - July 26, 2024 -NBCUniversal (\\\"NBCU\\\") announced today that it will showcase segments of its coverage of the 2024 Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony on Sphere's fully programmable LED exterior - the Exosphere - in Las Vegas, Nev., tonight, Friday, July 26.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 68, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999998544808, \"rank\": 1.452977390527515e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 113, \"end\": 117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 130, \"end\": 140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Coast_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999993447091, \"rank\": 5.677040789159975e-10, \"text\": \"West Coast\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Coast_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Coast_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 203, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982529517892, \"rank\": 1.0413529915795714e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 535, \"end\": 544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"score\": 0.999998740628027, \"rank\": 1.2593618678686969e-06, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Ashworth\", \"score\": 0.939936096385017, \"rank\": 0.03345454263236227, \"text\": \"Nev\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Ashworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neville_Ashworth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The initiative will be in partnership with Sphere Entertainment Co.  \\\"The Opening Ceremony is unlike any other event, bringing the world together on the grandest stage,\\\" saidJenny Storms, Chief Marketing Officer, Entertainment and Sports, NBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 830, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3252417032928285e-15, \"text\": \"Sphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\"}, {\"begin\": 817, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 0.9999999930637387, \"rank\": 6.936369684545584e-09, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are excited to display some of its most exciting moments on Sphere's Exosphere, which continues to captivate the world with its electrifying creativity.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 895, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3252417032928285e-15, \"text\": \"Sphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\"}, {\"begin\": 904, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0371942045478968e-21, \"text\": \"Exosphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether it's Team USA and France sailing down the Seine or the lighting of the Olympic cauldron, this activation will provide viewers with an extraordinary viewing experience fit for the grandeur and history unfolding in Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 988, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999990127435, \"rank\": 9.833248238119692e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1014, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982529517892, \"rank\": 1.0413529915795714e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1038, \"end\": 1043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0053337747393556e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7646748655043633e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the Paris Olympics Opening Ceremony is making history by taking place on one of the world's most famous waterways, the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999998544808, \"rank\": 1.452977390527515e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers will transform this iconic river into the world's largest theatrical stage for what promises to be one of the most spectacular Opening Ceremonies in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of walking into a stadium, a four-mile-long flotilla of nearly 90 boats will carry athletes from more than 200 countries past hundreds of thousands of spectators seated on the banks of the Seine.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0053337747393556e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"NBCU's Opening Ceremony presentation on the Exosphere, which will be simulcast during West Coast primetime coverage between 8:00-11:00 p.m. PT, is expected to include Team USA's and host nation France's boats finishing their journey down the River Seine, passing the Eiffel Tower and Trocadero, as well as the ceremonial lighting of the Olympic cauldron.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 2097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1743, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9999999998544808, \"rank\": 1.452977390527515e-10, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}, {\"begin\": 1787, \"end\": 1796, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0371942045478968e-21, \"text\": \"Exosphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\"}, {\"begin\": 1910, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999990127435, \"rank\": 9.833248238119692e-10, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1937, \"end\": 1943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999982529517892, \"rank\": 1.0413529915795714e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2027, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.9999891000568971, \"rank\": 1.0889938099454581e-05, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This will mark the first time that key moments from a global event will be simulcast on the Exosphere - the world's largest LED screen.\", \"from\": 2098, \"to\": 2233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sphere is a global landmark, and we are honored that NBCU has elected to bring the world's biggest event to the Exosphere in a first-of-its-kind collaboration,\\\" saidJennifer Koester, President and Chief Operating Officer, Sphere Entertainment.\", \"from\": 2235, \"to\": 2479, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2289, \"end\": 2293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCU\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}, {\"begin\": 2348, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0371942045478968e-21, \"text\": \"Exosphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exosphere\"}, {\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3252417032928285e-15, \"text\": \"Sphere\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sphere\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sphere is about bringing people together to share in immersive experiences and we are proud to use this canvas to celebrate NBC's coverage as the Paris Olympic Games begin.\\\"\", \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2605, \"end\": 2608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9983040404477801, \"rank\": 0.0016977616159276846, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening Ceremony coverage will be hosted by NBC Olympics primetime hostMike Tiricoalongside Emmy Award-winning talk show host and Grammy Award-winning artistKelly Clarksonand Pro Football Hall of Fame quarterback and two-time Super Bowl championPeyton Manning, and will feature NBC Sports'Maria Tayloron the Team USA boat, andTODAY ShowhostsSavannah GuthrieandHoda Kotbon a bridge along the route.\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Olympic_broadcasts\"}, {\"begin\": 2786, \"end\": 2792, \"title\": \"http://db